// EXPECT: type_fail
//ERR: cannot assign str to 'x'

// Fixed-type rule (3b): a variable's type is fixed at its declaration. A bare
// reassignment must FIT that type; retyping an int variable to str is a
// conformance error, not a silent widen. (Use an explicit `: any` or a union
// annotation if a variable genuinely needs to hold more than one type.)
var x <- 1;
x <- "two";
print(x);
